    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-01-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="12"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Conference W and PW/1–1745</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Honduran Ambassador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cáceres</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>The Ambassador of Honduras presents his compliments to His Excellency the
                    Secretary of State and has the honor to thank him for his courtesy in having
                    sent him a copy of the memorandum containing the proposals<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d12fn16">See circular telegram, January 5, 3 p.m., <ref
                            target="#pg_1">p. 1</ref>.</note> made by His Excellency’s Government in
                    connection <pb facs="0023" n="9" xml:id="pg_9"/> with the forthcoming special
                    conference of the Governments of the American Republics.</p>
                <p>The Ambassador of Honduras advises at this time that his Government accepts the
                    invitation of the Government of Mexico to the aforementioned conference which
                    will open on the 15th of next February, and that it has designated Dr. Julián R.
                    Cáceres as Chairman of the delegation; Engineer Gregorio Reyes Zelaya as
                    Delegate; and Mr. Juan Angel Paz as Secretary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. R. C[<hi rend="smallcaps">áceres</hi>]</signed>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-01-17">January 17,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
